{
  "name": "Focusing Bloodshed",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "modules/pf1spheres/assets/icons/spheres/duelist.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>After causing a creature to begin bleeding, you may spend a move action to regain your martial focus. As part of this move action, you may make a melee touch attack as a free action against a non-bleeding creature within reach. This attack deals no damage, but causes that creature to begin bleeding as per your blooded strike. (This does not allow you to apply a (bleed) talent.) Additionally, when an enemy causes you to begin bleeding, you may spend an immediate action to regain your martial focus.</p>\n<p><strong>Author's Note:</strong> For the intents of this talent, \"begin bleeding\" refers to any application of a new source of bleed damage that the creature did not already suffer from, rather than causing a creature to begin bleeding for the first time.</p>\n",
